runs.comm: super one first up, hits the deck just outside off and seams away, the keeper pouching tidily, Broad having rolled his fingers over that one
tight down the channel again, good length, and left alone
defended on the front foot
brings down the bat straight and gets an outside edge which skews well wide of the first slip
comes outside off to miss it, eagerly on the attack of course from the off, and then notes the good length and respectfully shoulders arms
squares behind it now outside off, playing back down the line
got him! Anderson strikes first ball, How drives hard at it and as it moves away off the seam, it's taken well at first slip by Shah
has him fending at this one first up, Marshall squaring behind it and the ball sails through
outside edge bounces down in front of the second slip, Shah, who has been placed there only very recently
outside-edged quickly down to third man where a diving Bopara tidies up just inside the rope
pushed through the channel, another good length
pushed on to a good length, the batsman presses down and they shuffle through quickly
width outside off and the batsman cuts hard out to point
too much width outside off but Wright spares the blushes with a sharp diving effort at gully
shortish one, but he hardly times it, his shoulders muscling the ball out towards deep midwicket
goes fuller, but it's a gift really outside off, and Marshall leans into a well-struck cover drive, now that one had plenty of timing and Pietersen is quick to give it up for dead
no run this time, the batsman playing off the back foot but not quite getting his shot right
another one for England! Broad strikes this time, Marshall edging through - he had been looking to hit the ball to point or third man - and this time he cuts right into the keeper's hands
some good lift for Anderson there, nearly foxing the batsman, who goes on the back foot correctly but the rise through deceives him
McCullum jumps into a leave this time, quickly shouldering arms as it goes through
McCullum's out of his crease, alert, but Anderson forces him into the defensive on the back foot with a straight, well-pitched delivery
a huge shout and point from Anderson but immediately Umpire Gould turns it down

comes out diagonally, a quick bouncer from Anderson outside off ricochets hard off the helmet and out to the man at gully. England show no sympathy, immediately appealing for the catch. He's clearly not out and nods his head just to show he's OK
outside off, lets this one go through now
outside off and driven hard off the back foot but straight to the man at cover
defended hard down the track on the front foot
overpitched a touch in line with off, a forceful drive out to mid-on but it's snapped up easily
a crashing drive through the covers hit hard, Taylor really launching himself on his front foot and into the shot
full delivery, driven on the up to mid off now
Broad's running in as if his life depending on it, and it's worked out to the covers
picked up off the toes and driven out in front of midwicket, well timed up and over
six this time! Down on one knee and gives it the kneel-and-deliver treatment launched over deep backward square leg. It wasn't too bad a ball, either
more respect for Andrson this time, a defence right back down the line in front of off
pure timing and that is boomed off the front foot through the covers. Extraordinary power and timing combination
defended on the front foot
nips back in off the seam and Taylor looks to cut it out to point but doesn't quite get hold of it
puts so much effort into this that he falls over in delivery, the ball's pushed back past him, Pietersen picks it up and side-arms at the sticks, missing
pushed out on the front foot
plenty of width outside off, draws Taylor into the shot and it goes past the outside edge
slower delivery in line with middle and off, defended on the front foot
hey now, shot and a half, Taylor tees off with a straight drive that travels flat and barely got up off the ground at all. Coo-ee, that was a good hit, very golf-like
good reply from Wright, hustling it past the outside edge
donw the legs and MucCullum is quick to flick it off the pads through to deep square
outside off and he's deceived by the pace, rushing at it, but can't connect
goes on one knee and tries to pull it round behind square, and indeed does so, but without much timing
bowled him! Great delivery to remove Taylor, nipping back in from outside off to clean up the batsman whose middle stump rocks back and he's on his way
defended down off the back foot and they shuffle through from the dab-and-go, Anderson tidying up as the ball goes to gully
turned off the legs behind square and a straight throw may have been interesting... Collingwood stretching to his left to snap it up
banged in short outside off, a hard swivel-pull picked up by Swann in front of midwicket, didn't get hold of that properly
pushed off the legs this time
not too sure where that one went, squeezed down on it behind the stumps
banged in again down off and Styris is certainly tempted into the pull but nearly gets the under edge
throws in the slower ball which is nearly a wide outside off, drawing in the batsman to play way away from the body
slower one, forces the drive on the up, pushed out to Bell at mid off who tidies up without fuss
outside off, McCullum drives out but straight to the covers
outside off, cut hard out to point but only the single
driven on the front foot out to the covers, fairly square
pushed wide outside off, cut into the covers this time and they take an overthrow as Shah's throw comes in sloppily
width and also short, and McCullum picks up his first boundary with a hard cut
better ball, but a single is squeezed out to mid off
back in the crease, he has to settle for an old-fashioned block
swung from short outside off stump, it sounded as if he had hit it with a lump of old oak but it still carried over midwicket ... by about an inch
short and straighter, hooked but this one dribbles along the ground to Pietersen out in the deep ... dreaming of how many noughts his bank balance will have after November ... he hopes
slower and wider, cut through the covers with no real pace

peach in 50, 40 or 20-over cricket ... held up, yorker straight through McCullum who indicates with lots of overt blinking that he might actually have lost that in the flight. He played all round it and he's on his way
back and defensively pushed to shortish mid-off
pushed gently square on the off side, the rare Twenty20 sight of an ambled single
good old-fashioned offbreak at no more than a crawl, thrown up outside stump, Fulton plays all round it and it creeps between bat and pad
dropped ...tossed up, a slash and Collingwood, who has gambled by bringing himself in at slip, spills a sharp chance. Awkward height but still ...
into the pads, a loud appeal
pushed into the off side, no real intent ...
a nothing flick into the leg side, a thick edge into the pad and the ball plops out towards midwicket
back of a length and wide outside off, thumped along the ground to deep cover
ugly swish across the line, he misses, a rasping appeal but Peter Hartley not having any of it
turned into the off side
back and cut hard to deep cover, again a lot of shot for one run
pushed to Broad who does well at mid-on because the ball kicked off one of the old creases
swings across the line , misses, and you have to say, at this point New Zealand's batsmen look horribly out of sorts
hit high over the covers with no real power
back, leading edge and it drops a yard or so out of Swann's reach as he scurries to the right round the non striker
pushed behind square on the off ... a single and England will be more than happy to give them that
cut behind square, backward point fields but can't save the single
whipped off the pads to deep backward square leg who is in from the rope in a jiffy
swung-swept from outside off, not timed, and Shah trundles round from behind square in the deep to field
a big-looking shot doesn't go far into the on side
punched off the back foot, a diving Collingwood fields with a dive at short extra cover
worked to deepish midwicket ... just the single again
that's better, rocks back and heaves a long-hop over wide midwicket .. it carries by a foot
opens the face but can't beat point
fuller, crisp drive to deep mid-off
hard drive through Collingwood at short cover, technically a catch but it almost pole-axed him
another single offered and accepted
horrible swish from outside off just about gets to deepish midwicket
back and paddled uppishly to wide midwicket
off drive to long-on
uses his feet but can do no more than a firm push to deep cover
back and dropped with sift hands to backward point
straight, Styris pulls, misses, and the ball thuds into the top of his middle and leg stumps
slower ball, patted to mid-off and about eight fielders converge
outside off, he misses with an attempted dab
nurdled into the leg side
pushed to cover for a single
he skips down the pitch like a man stepping off a cliff, misses by some way and doesn't even try to get back as Ambrose flicks off the bails
flicks, misses, a loud appeal but he was well outside the line
flatter and quicker, he goes back and pushes into the off side but has to hurry to make the run
tossed up, he sweeps out of the blockhole to deep midwicket
worked into the on side, again a cantered single
tossed up once more, hit uppishly to wide long-on
short, Vettori has already stepped outside off and he works the ball past fine leg who was up in the circle
again Vettori heads to leg but misses and the ball passes over the stumps
this time he shimmies to leg, driving on the half volley square into the off side
full, almost a yorker, driven firmly and straight, Vettori is on for the two from the off and he makes it with ease to the danger end
streaky ... straight, a swing, a thick inside edge misses leg stump and beats fine leg who is still in the circle
good shot, driven on the half volley over extra cover and it beats long-off
slower, shorter ball outside off, a tennis-style paddle to third man
attempted yorker but it is a low full-toss which he scoops high to Ian Bell at long-on ... seven or eight yards off the rope but that comes down with snow on it
he steps a yard outside leg, Anderson follows and it still passes outside his leg stump
wide full toss, helped down to third man
full and swinging in, a thick outside edge scoots to third man
slower ball, a weary-looking heave to midwicket
short, pulled from in front of his visor to square leg, Gillespie comes back for the second but he's never even in the frame
